(numFetchBufferEntries, power_pad).explanation: Fetch buffer entries are internal processor structures that do not directly affect pad power consumption, which is primarily related to I/O interface power;

(numFetchBufferEntries, power_switching).explanation: Increasing the number of fetch buffer entries directly increases switching activity as more storage elements transition states during fetch operations;

(numFetchBufferEntries, time).explanation: The number of fetch buffer entries affects performance metrics like CPI but does not directly determine execution time, which depends on multiple factors;
